<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFCBFFC61687F97CFD685E8F" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFCBFFC61687F97CFD685E8F" blockId="19.[151,1437,1613,2036]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC61687F97CFE805F8C" bold="true" box="[199,338,1757,1783]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCBFFC61720F97FFDE55F83" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[352,567,1758,1784]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Meroles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anchietae">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC61720F97FFDE55F83" box="[352,567,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Meroles anchietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Namib Desert (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCBFFC615A5F97FFB535F83" author="Branch, W. R." box="[997,1153,1758,1784]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref34648" refString="Branch, W. R. (1998) Field Guide to Snakes and Other Reptiles of Southern Africa, 3 rd edition. Struik Publishers, Cape Town, 328 pp." type="book" year="1998">Branch 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCBFFC612D5F97FFA435F83" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1173,1425,1758,1784]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC61345F97FFA975F83" box="[1285,1349,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Ferreira never published the Newton Expedition specimens but identified the extant specimens as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCBFFC612BEF8A3FED65E3B" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pachyrhyncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anchietae">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC612BEF8A3FED65E3B" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Pachyrhyncus anchietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as noted by the extant labels. 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCBFFC61417F887FC9A5E3B" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[599,840,1830,1856]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC61480F887FD255E3B" box="[704,759,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
referenced specimens MHNCUP/REP 219–222 from “Mossamedes” when discussing the species’ taxonomy and distribution. Up until recently, 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCBFFC612D4F8EBFAF55E1F" box="[1172,1319,1866,1892]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pachyrhyncus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anchietae">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC612D4F8EBFAF55E1F" box="[1172,1319,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. anchietae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFCBFFC6130AF8EBFA4E5E1F" box="[1354,1436,1866,1892]" name="Angola" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Angola</collectingCountry>
was only known from its 
<typeStatus id="E715FA9CFFCBFFC617F6F8CFFE345EF3" box="[438,486,1902,1928]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
locality “Rio Coroca, dans le littoral de Mossamedes”, but collections by 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCBFFC6136AF8CFFEC05ED7" author="Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; De Sa, S. A. C. &amp; Bandeira, S. &amp; Valerio, H. &amp; Stanley, E. L. &amp; Kuhn, A. L. &amp; Marques, M. P. &amp; Vindum, J. V. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="15 - 61" refId="ref35490" refString="Ceriaco, L. M. P., De Sa, S. A. C., Bandeira, S., Valerio, H., Stanley, E. L., Kuhn, A. L., Marques, M. P., Vindum, J. V., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2016 a) Herpetological survey of the Iona National Park and Namibe National Park, Angola, with a synoptic list of the amphibians and reptiles of Namibe Province, southwestern Angola. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 63 (2), 15 - 61." type="journal article" year="2016">
Ceríaco 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCBFFC613C8F8CFFF665ED7" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(2016a)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that the species has a broader distribution range, even if confined to the Namib Desert regions. The species was recently collected by Luís M. P. Ceríaco and Mariana P. Marques in the same area where Newton collected the aforementioned specimens (
<figureCitation id="A09558BBFFCBFFC61427F87BFD7E5E8F" box="[615,684,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1061,1085]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1035]" captionTargetId="figure-33@20.[151,1436,179,1035]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Life photo of Meroles anchietae, from Baía dos Tigres. Photo by Luis Ceríaco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5453981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5453981/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
